Note:
Runa Scientific Computing: Sparse Linear Algebra (Compatibility Layer)

This is a compatibility wrapper that imports from the unified math linear algebra engine.
All functionality has been moved to math/engine/linalg for better architecture.
:End Note

Import "math/engine/linalg/sparse" as SparseEngine

Note: Re-export sparse matrix types
Type SparseMatrix is SparseEngine.SparseMatrix
Type SparseFormat is SparseEngine.SparseFormat

Note: Re-export sparse matrix creation
Process called "create_sparse_matrix" that takes data as Any and format as Any returns SparseMatrix:
    Return SparseEngine.create_sparse_matrix with data as data and format as format

Process called "sparse_from_dense" that takes dense_matrix as Any returns SparseMatrix:
    Return SparseEngine.sparse_from_dense with dense_matrix as dense_matrix

Process called "sparse_to_dense" that takes sparse_matrix as SparseMatrix returns Any:
    Return SparseEngine.sparse_to_dense with sparse_matrix as sparse_matrix

Note: Re-export sparse operations
Process called "sparse_multiply" that takes a as SparseMatrix and b as Any returns Any:
    Return SparseEngine.sparse_multiply with a as a and b as b

Process called "sparse_add" that takes a as SparseMatrix and b as SparseMatrix returns SparseMatrix:
    Return SparseEngine.sparse_add with a as a and b as b

Process called "sparse_transpose" that takes matrix as SparseMatrix returns SparseMatrix:
    Return SparseEngine.sparse_transpose with matrix as matrix

Process called "sparse_solve" that takes a as SparseMatrix and b as Any returns Any:
    Return SparseEngine.sparse_solve with a as a and b as b